{"id":41346,"date":"2023-10-04T23:07:30","date_gmt":"2023-10-04T19:07:30","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=41346"},"modified":"2025-07-04T11:22:45","modified_gmt":"2025-07-04T07:22:45","slug":"advise-not-to-curse","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/10\/04\/advise-not-to-curse\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Cursing: I advise you not to curse others"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Jurmuz al-Hujaymi reported: I said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, advise me.\u201d The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>I advise you not to curse others.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 20678<\/p>\n<p>Grade:\u00a0<em><strong>Sahih<\/strong> <\/em>(authentic) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p>Imam al-Ghazali commented, \u201cClose to cursing is supplication for evil against a person, even supplication against a wrongdoer, such as asking Allah to never give them bodily health or peace and so on, for that is reprehensible. In the narrations, the oppressed will continue to supplicate against the wrongdoer until he is sufficiently recompensed, then what is beyond that is a surplus in favor of the wrongdoer on the Day of Resurrection.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Ih\u0323ya\u0304\u2019 Ulu\u0304m al-Di\u0304n 3\/126<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u062c\u064f\u0631\u0652\u0645\u064f\u0648\u0632\u064d \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0647\u064f\u062c\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0645\u0650\u064a \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064f\u0644\u0652\u062a\u064f \u064a\u064e\u0627 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650 \u0623\u064e\u0648\u0652\u0635\u0650\u0646\u0650\u064a \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0623\u064f\u0648\u0635\u0650